  <title>GLib.FormatSizeFlags</title>
  <p>Flags to modify the format of the string returned by <link xref="GLib.format_size_full"/>.</p>

<terms>
<item>
<title><code>FormatSizeFlags.DEFAULT</code></title>
  <p>behave the same as <link xref="GLib.format_size"/></p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>FormatSizeFlags.LONG_FORMAT</code></title>
  <p>include the exact number of bytes as part
    of the returned string.  For example, "45.6 kB (45,612 bytes)".</p>
</item>
<item>
<title><code>FormatSizeFlags.IEC_UNITS</code></title>
  <p>use IEC (base 1024) units with "KiB"-style
    suffixes. IEC units should only be used for reporting things with
    a strong "power of 2" basis, like RAM sizes or RAID stripe sizes.
    Network and storage sizes should be reported in the normal SI units.</p>
</item>
